analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Neutral regime persists amid trade policy clarity. The 52 GMS score maintains a cautious equilibrium within Phase 2, though the judiciary's revocation of trade barriers catalyzes immediate volatility compression. While VIX retracement and credit spread stability suggest risk appetite, the profound divergence in market breadth and precious metal appreciation signify defensive positioning against underlying regime fragility. Navigate the fiscal-monetary nexus via high-conviction cyclicals. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
